tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated hemoglobin and MCHC, which may suggest hemoconcentration or possible underlying erythrocytosis; clinical correlation is advised. Platelet count is normal, but platelet distribution width is markedly increased, possibly indicating platelet anisocytosis or activation. Other parameters are within normal limits. Further evaluation may be warranted depending on clinical context.
